OL,3,CLifeguards could have deterred death
OL,4,Cof teenager who jumped from pier
OL,6,F"This tragic incident happened on
OL,7,Fprivate land. The RNLI works with
OL,8,Flandowners and Councils to provide
OL,9,Flifeguard patrols when they are
OL,10,Frequested by the landowners and have
OL,11,Fexplicit permission to do so.
OL,12,FProviding lifeguard cover is one of a
OL,13,Frange of safety measures a landowner
OL,14,For Council can implement to mitigate
OL,15,Frisk. Other measures such as permanent
OL,16,Fsignage or beach safety education are
OL,17,Fimportant as lifeguards cannot be
OL,18,Feverywhere all of the time. This is
OL,19,Fwhy the RNLI invests in sharing water
OL,20,Fsafety advice with the public, so
OL,21,Fpeople have the information they need
OL,22,Fto keep themselves safe.
